{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":837,"text":"I want you to look\naround the room for a minute"},{"time":3128,"text":"and try to find the most\nparanoid person here --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5871,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6959,"text":"And then I want you to point\nat that person for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9435,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10494,"text":"OK, don't actually do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11877,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13020,"text":"But, as an organizational psychologist,"},{"time":14913,"text":"I spend a lot of time in workplaces,"},{"time":16819,"text":"and I find paranoia everywhere."},{"time":19532,"text":"Paranoia is caused by people\nthat I call \"takers.\""},{"time":21965,"text":"Takers are self-serving\nin their interactions."},{"time":24172,"text":"It's all about what can you do for me."},{"time":26832,"text":"The opposite is a giver."},{"time":28257,"text":"It's somebody who approaches\nmost interactions by asking,"},{"time":31041,"text":"\"What can I do for you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33165,"text":"I wanted to give you a chance\nto think about your own style."},{"time":36060,"text":"We all have moments of giving and taking."},{"time":38037,"text":"Your style is how you treat\nmost of the people most of the time,"},{"time":41077,"text":"your default."},{"time":42259,"text":"I have a short test you can take"},{"time":43825,"text":"to figure out if you're more\nof a giver or a taker,"},{"time":46348,"text":"and you can take it right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47850,"text":"[The Narcissist Test]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49313,"text":"[Step 1: Take a moment\nto think about yourself.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51649,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52776,"text":"[Step 2: If you made it to Step 2,\nyou are not a narcissist.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55658,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58082,"text":"This is the only thing I will say today\nthat has no data behind it,"},{"time":61939,"text":"but I am convinced the longer it takes\nfor you to laugh at this cartoon,"},{"time":65395,"text":"the more worried we should be\nthat you're a taker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67846,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68935,"text":"Of course, not all takers are narcissists."},{"time":70991,"text":"Some are just givers who got burned\none too many times."},{"time":73903,"text":"Then there's another kind of taker\nthat we won't be addressing today,"},{"time":77251,"text":"and that's called a psychopath."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79128,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80303,"text":"I was curious, though, about how\ncommon these extremes are,"},{"time":83199,"text":"and so I surveyed over 30,000\npeople across industries"},{"time":86032,"text":"around the world's cultures."},{"time":87668,"text":"And I found that most people\nare right in the middle"},{"time":90170,"text":"between giving and taking."},{"time":91660,"text":"They choose this third style\ncalled \"matching.\""},{"time":94029,"text":"If you're a matcher, you try to keep\nan even balance of give and take:"},{"time":97398,"text":"quid pro quo -- I'll do something\nfor you if you do something for me."},{"time":100740,"text":"And that seems like a safe way\nto live your life."},{"time":103145,"text":"But is it the most effective\nand productive way to live your life?"},{"time":106353,"text":"The answer to that question\nis a very definitive ..."},{"time":108841,"text":"maybe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110023,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111273,"text":"I studied dozens of organizations,"},{"time":113476,"text":"thousands of people."},{"time":114675,"text":"I had engineers measuring\ntheir productivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118251,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120630,"text":"I looked at medical students' grades --"},{"time":123623,"text":"even salespeople's revenue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125622,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127092,"text":"And, unexpectedly,"},{"time":128768,"text":"the worst performers in each\nof these jobs were the givers."},{"time":132749,"text":"The engineers who got the least work done"},{"time":134817,"text":"were the ones who did more favors\nthan they got back."},{"time":137347,"text":"They were so busy doing\nother people's jobs,"},{"time":139507,"text":"they literally ran out of time and energy\nto get their own work completed."},{"time":143081,"text":"In medical school, the lowest grades\nbelong to the students"},{"time":145910,"text":"who agree most strongly\nwith statements like,"},{"time":148041,"text":"\"I love helping others,\""},{"time":151068,"text":"which suggests the doctor\nyou ought to trust"},{"time":153316,"text":"is the one who came to med school\nwith no desire to help anybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156419,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":157470,"text":"And then in sales, too,\nthe lowest revenue accrued"},{"time":159852,"text":"in the most generous salespeople."},{"time":161571,"text":"I actually reached out\nto one of those salespeople"},{"time":164025,"text":"who had a very high giver score."},{"time":165656,"text":"And I asked him, \"Why do\nyou suck at your job --\""},{"time":168238,"text":"I didn't ask it that way, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169803,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170871,"text":"\"What's the cost of generosity in sales?\""},{"time":173247,"text":"And he said, \"Well, I just care\nso deeply about my customers"},{"time":176537,"text":"that I would never sell them\none of our crappy products.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":179323,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180748,"text":"So just out of curiosity,"},{"time":182000,"text":"how many of you self-identify more\nas givers than takers or matchers?"},{"time":185308,"text":"Raise your hands."},{"time":186962,"text":"OK, it would have been more\nbefore we talked about these data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190525,"text":"But actually, it turns out\nthere's a twist here,"},{"time":194176,"text":"because givers are often\nsacrificing themselves,"},{"time":197496,"text":"but they make their organizations better."},{"time":200345,"text":"We have a huge body of evidence --"},{"time":203136,"text":"many, many studies looking\nat the frequency of giving behavior"},{"time":206893,"text":"that exists in a team\nor an organization --"},{"time":209054,"text":"and the more often people are helping\nand sharing their knowledge"},{"time":212164,"text":"and providing mentoring,"},{"time":213341,"text":"the better organizations do\non every metric we can measure:"},{"time":216142,"text":"higher profits, customer satisfaction,\nemployee retention --"},{"time":218997,"text":"even lower operating expenses."},{"time":221407,"text":"So givers spend a lot of time\ntrying to help other people"},{"time":224299,"text":"and improve the team,"},{"time":225530,"text":"and then, unfortunately,\nthey suffer along the way."},{"time":228030,"text":"I want to talk about what it takes"},{"time":229722,"text":"to build cultures where givers\nactually get to succeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233564,"text":"So I wondered, then, if givers\nare the worst performers,"},{"time":236608,"text":"who are the best performers?"},{"time":239438,"text":"Let me start with the good news:\nit's not the takers."},{"time":242112,"text":"Takers tend to rise quickly\nbut also fall quickly in most jobs."},{"time":245791,"text":"And they fall at the hands of matchers."},{"time":247912,"text":"If you're a matcher, you believe\nin \"An eye for an eye\" -- a just world."},{"time":251356,"text":"And so when you meet a taker,"},{"time":252800,"text":"you feel like it's your mission in life"},{"time":254693,"text":"to just punish the hell\nout of that person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256759,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257797,"text":"And that way justice gets served."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260108,"text":"Well, most people are matchers."},{"time":262102,"text":"And that means if you're a taker,"},{"time":263710,"text":"it tends to catch up with you eventually;"},{"time":265714,"text":"what goes around will come around."},{"time":267376,"text":"And so the logical conclusion is:"},{"time":269006,"text":"it must be the matchers\nwho are the best performers."},{"time":271895,"text":"But they're not."},{"time":273437,"text":"In every job, in every organization\nI've ever studied,"},{"time":276311,"text":"the best results belong\nto the givers again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279651,"text":"Take a look at some data I gathered\nfrom hundreds of salespeople,"},{"time":282833,"text":"tracking their revenue."},{"time":284010,"text":"What you can see is that the givers\ngo to both extremes."},{"time":286689,"text":"They make up the majority of people\nwho bring in the lowest revenue,"},{"time":289931,"text":"but also the highest revenue."},{"time":291421,"text":"The same patterns were true\nfor engineers' productivity"},{"time":294049,"text":"and medical students' grades."},{"time":295464,"text":"Givers are overrepresented\nat the bottom and at the top"},{"time":298095,"text":"of every success metric that I can track."},{"time":300201,"text":"Which raises the question:"},{"time":301527,"text":"How do we create a world\nwhere more of these givers get to excel?"},{"time":304960,"text":"I want to talk about how to do that,\nnot just in businesses,"},{"time":307807,"text":"but also in nonprofits, schools --"},{"time":309662,"text":"even governments."},{"time":310979,"text":"Are you ready?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312209,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313419,"text":"I was going to do it anyway,\nbut I appreciate the enthusiasm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316435,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":317482,"text":"The first thing that's really critical"},{"time":319350,"text":"is to recognize that givers\nare your most valuable people,"},{"time":322121,"text":"but if they're not careful, they burn out."},{"time":324579,"text":"So you have to protect\nthe givers in your midst."},{"time":327093,"text":"And I learned a great lesson about this\nfrom Fortune's best networker."},{"time":332993,"text":"It's the guy, not the cat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334367,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335551,"text":"His name is Adam Rifkin."},{"time":337331,"text":"He's a very successful serial entrepreneur"},{"time":339567,"text":"who spends a huge amount\nof his time helping other people."},{"time":342385,"text":"And his secret weapon\nis the five-minute favor."},{"time":345261,"text":"Adam said, \"You don't have to be\nMother Teresa or Gandhi"},{"time":347944,"text":"to be a giver."},{"time":349151,"text":"You just have to find small ways\nto add large value"},{"time":351678,"text":"to other people's lives.\""},{"time":353059,"text":"That could be as simple\nas making an introduction"},{"time":355426,"text":"between two people who could\nbenefit from knowing each other."},{"time":358381,"text":"It could be sharing your knowledge\nor giving a little bit of feedback."},{"time":361742,"text":"Or It might be even something\nas basic as saying,"},{"time":364078,"text":"\"You know,"},{"time":365331,"text":"I'm going to try and figure out"},{"time":366855,"text":"if I can recognize somebody\nwhose work has gone unnoticed.\""},{"time":370462,"text":"And those five-minute favors\nare really critical"},{"time":372780,"text":"to helping givers set boundaries\nand protect themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375962,"text":"The second thing that matters"},{"time":377431,"text":"if you want to build a culture\nwhere givers succeed,"},{"time":379923,"text":"is you actually need a culture\nwhere help-seeking is the norm;"},{"time":382872,"text":"where people ask a lot."},{"time":384536,"text":"This may hit a little too close\nto home for some of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387229,"text":"[So in all your relationships,\nyou always have to be the giver?]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":390292,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391340,"text":"What you see with successful givers"},{"time":393095,"text":"is they recognize that it's OK\nto be a receiver, too."},{"time":396754,"text":"If you run an organization,\nwe can actually make this easier."},{"time":399641,"text":"We can make it easier\nfor people to ask for help."},{"time":401962,"text":"A couple colleagues and I\nstudied hospitals."},{"time":404058,"text":"We found that on certain floors,\nnurses did a lot of help-seeking,"},{"time":407284,"text":"and on other floors,\nthey did very little of it."},{"time":409559,"text":"The factor that stood out on the floors\nwhere help-seeking was common,"},{"time":412929,"text":"where it was the norm,"},{"time":414104,"text":"was there was just one nurse\nwhose sole job it was"},{"time":416503,"text":"to help other nurses on the unit."},{"time":418558,"text":"When that role was available,"},{"time":419963,"text":"nurses said, \"It's not embarrassing,\nit's not vulnerable to ask for help --"},{"time":423644,"text":"it's actually encouraged.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426263,"text":"Help-seeking isn't important\njust for protecting the success"},{"time":429113,"text":"and the well-being of givers."},{"time":430536,"text":"It's also critical to getting\nmore people to act like givers,"},{"time":433492,"text":"because the data say"},{"time":434705,"text":"that somewhere between 75 and 90 percent\nof all giving in organizations"},{"time":438129,"text":"starts with a request."},{"time":439996,"text":"But a lot of people don't ask."},{"time":441468,"text":"They don't want to look incompetent,"},{"time":443240,"text":"they don't know where to turn,\nthey don't want to burden others."},{"time":446291,"text":"Yet if nobody ever asks for help,"},{"time":448024,"text":"you have a lot of frustrated givers\nin your organization"},{"time":450723,"text":"who would love to step up and contribute,"},{"time":452730,"text":"if they only knew\nwho could benefit and how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455413,"text":"But I think the most important thing,"},{"time":457235,"text":"if you want to build a culture\nof successful givers,"},{"time":459735,"text":"is to be thoughtful about who\nyou let onto your team."},{"time":462561,"text":"I figured, you want a culture\nof productive generosity,"},{"time":465601,"text":"you should hire a bunch of givers."},{"time":467597,"text":"But I was surprised to discover, actually,\nthat that was not right --"},{"time":471715,"text":"that the negative impact\nof a taker on a culture"},{"time":474214,"text":"is usually double to triple\nthe positive impact of a giver."},{"time":477530,"text":"Think about it this way:"},{"time":478704,"text":"one bad apple can spoil a barrel,"},{"time":480392,"text":"but one good egg\njust does not make a dozen."},{"time":483942,"text":"I don't know what that means --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":485518,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486661,"text":"But I hope you do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488058,"text":"No -- let even one taker into a team,"},{"time":491404,"text":"and you will see that the givers\nwill stop helping."},{"time":494648,"text":"They'll say, \"I'm surrounded\nby a bunch of snakes and sharks."},{"time":497602,"text":"Why should I contribute?\""},{"time":498992,"text":"Whereas if you let one giver into a team,"},{"time":500992,"text":"you don't get an explosion of generosity."},{"time":503138,"text":"More often, people are like,"},{"time":504583,"text":"\"Great! That person can do all our work.\""},{"time":507077,"text":"So, effective hiring and screening\nand team building"},{"time":509847,"text":"is not about bringing in the givers;"},{"time":512007,"text":"it's about weeding out the takers."},{"time":515036,"text":"If you can do that well,"},{"time":516211,"text":"you'll be left with givers and matchers."},{"time":518177,"text":"The givers will be generous"},{"time":519566,"text":"because they don't have to worry\nabout the consequences."},{"time":522224,"text":"And the beauty of the matchers\nis that they follow the norm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525361,"text":"So how do you catch a taker\nbefore it's too late?"},{"time":528745,"text":"We're actually pretty bad\nat figuring out who's a taker,"},{"time":531656,"text":"especially on first impressions."},{"time":533506,"text":"There's a personality trait\nthat throws us off."},{"time":535838,"text":"It's called agreeableness,"},{"time":537167,"text":"one the major dimensions\nof personality across cultures."},{"time":539812,"text":"Agreeable people are warm and friendly,\nthey're nice, they're polite."},{"time":543321,"text":"You find a lot of them in Canada --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":545136,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":546763,"text":"Where there was actually\na national contest"},{"time":550284,"text":"to come up with a new Canadian slogan\nand fill in the blank,"},{"time":553338,"text":"\"As Canadian as ...\""},{"time":554937,"text":"I thought the winning entry\nwas going to be,"},{"time":557045,"text":"\"As Canadian as maple syrup,\"\nor, \"... ice hockey.\""},{"time":559540,"text":"But no, Canadians voted\nfor their new national slogan to be --"},{"time":562549,"text":"I kid you not --"},{"time":563734,"text":"\"As Canadian as possible\nunder the circumstances.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":566189,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570020,"text":"Now for those of you\nwho are highly agreeable,"},{"time":572415,"text":"or maybe slightly Canadian,"},{"time":573832,"text":"you get this right away."},{"time":575229,"text":"How could I ever say I'm any one thing"},{"time":577070,"text":"when I'm constantly adapting\nto try to please other people?"},{"time":580400,"text":"Disagreeable people do less of it."},{"time":582247,"text":"They're more critical,\nskeptical, challenging,"},{"time":585208,"text":"and far more likely than their peers\nto go to law school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588286,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589453,"text":"That's not a joke,\nthat's actually an empirical fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592132,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":593215,"text":"So I always assumed\nthat agreeable people were givers"},{"time":595788,"text":"and disagreeable people were takers."},{"time":597759,"text":"But then I gathered the data,"},{"time":599213,"text":"and I was stunned to find\nno correlation between those traits,"},{"time":602350,"text":"because it turns out\nthat agreeableness-disagreeableness"},{"time":605033,"text":"is your outer veneer:"},{"time":606220,"text":"How pleasant is it to interact with you?"},{"time":608185,"text":"Whereas giving and taking\nare more of your inner motives:"},{"time":610901,"text":"What are your values?\nWhat are your intentions toward others?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":613817,"text":"If you really want to judge\npeople accurately,"},{"time":616033,"text":"you have to get to the moment every\nconsultant in the room is waiting for,"},{"time":619574,"text":"and draw a two-by-two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620763,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":625648,"text":"The agreeable givers are easy to spot:"},{"time":627679,"text":"they say yes to everything."},{"time":631740,"text":"The disagreeable takers\nare also recognized quickly,"},{"time":634637,"text":"although you might call them\nby a slightly different name."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638568,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":641828,"text":"We forget about the other\ntwo combinations."},{"time":643924,"text":"There are disagreeable givers\nin our organizations."},{"time":647283,"text":"There are people who are gruff\nand tough on the surface"},{"time":649948,"text":"but underneath have\nothers' best interests at heart."},{"time":653089,"text":"Or as an engineer put it,"},{"time":654476,"text":"\"Oh, disagreeable givers --"},{"time":656106,"text":"like somebody with a bad user interface\nbut a great operating system.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":660006,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661316,"text":"If that helps you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662711,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664424,"text":"Disagreeable givers are the most\nundervalued people in our organizations,"},{"time":667951,"text":"because they're the ones\nwho give the critical feedback"},{"time":670567,"text":"that no one wants to hear\nbut everyone needs to hear."},{"time":673197,"text":"We need to do a much better job\nvaluing these people"},{"time":675709,"text":"as opposed to writing them off early,"},{"time":677521,"text":"and saying, \"Eh, kind of prickly,"},{"time":679289,"text":"must be a selfish taker.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":681849,"text":"The other combination we forget about\nis the deadly one --"},{"time":684632,"text":"the agreeable taker,\nalso known as the faker."},{"time":688444,"text":"This is the person\nwho's nice to your face,"},{"time":690533,"text":"and then will stab you right in the back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692537,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694537,"text":"And my favorite way to catch\nthese people in the interview process"},{"time":697795,"text":"is to ask the question,"},{"time":699091,"text":"\"Can you give me the names of four people"},{"time":701077,"text":"whose careers you have\nfundamentally improved?\""},{"time":704424,"text":"The takers will give you four names,"},{"time":706341,"text":"and they will all be more\ninfluential than them,"},{"time":709062,"text":"because takers are great at kissing up\nand then kicking down."},{"time":712957,"text":"Givers are more likely to name people\nwho are below them in a hierarchy,"},{"time":716381,"text":"who don't have as much power,"},{"time":717951,"text":"who can do them no good."},{"time":719723,"text":"And let's face it, you all know\nyou can learn a lot about character"},{"time":722921,"text":"by watching how someone\ntreats their restaurant server"},{"time":725500,"text":"or their Uber driver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727319,"text":"So if we do all this well,"},{"time":728609,"text":"if we can weed takers\nout of organizations,"},{"time":730717,"text":"if we can make it safe to ask for help,"},{"time":732653,"text":"if we can protect givers from burnout"},{"time":734691,"text":"and make it OK for them to be ambitious\nin pursuing their own goals"},{"time":737942,"text":"as well as trying to help other people,"},{"time":740122,"text":"we can actually change the way\nthat people define success."},{"time":743053,"text":"Instead of saying it's all about\nwinning a competition,"},{"time":746429,"text":"people will realize success\nis really more about contribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750761,"text":"I believe that the most\nmeaningful way to succeed"},{"time":753146,"text":"is to help other people succeed."},{"time":755040,"text":"And if we can spread that belief,"},{"time":756735,"text":"we can actually turn paranoia upside down."},{"time":759410,"text":"There's a name for that."},{"time":760597,"text":"It's called \"pronoia.\""},{"time":763025,"text":"Pronoia is the delusional belief"},{"time":764746,"text":"that other people\nare plotting your well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767370,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":770908,"text":"That they're going around behind your back"},{"time":773485,"text":"and saying exceptionally\nglowing things about you."},{"time":777647,"text":"The great thing about a culture of givers\nis that's not a delusion --"},{"time":781480,"text":"it's reality."},{"time":783697,"text":"I want to live in a world\nwhere givers succeed,"},{"time":786297,"text":"and I hope you will help me\ncreate that world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788643,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789888,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}